    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <h3><a name="Description"></a><b>Description</b></h3>

<p>In the iOS app, when a user taps on an announcement and is redirected to a specific feature, navigating back does not return the user to the previously viewed announcement. Instead, it resets to the first announcement. This disrupts the user experience and makes it difficult to continue browsing announcements.</p>

<h3><a name="StepstoReproduce"></a><b>Steps to Reproduce</b></h3>

<ol>
	<li>Open the FP Agent App on an iOS device</li>
	<li>Go to the Announcements section</li>
	<li>Scroll to any announcement (not the first one)</li>
	<li>Tap on the announcement link to open the related feature</li>
	<li>Navigate back to the Announcements section</li>
</ol>


<h3><a name="ExpectedResult"></a><b>Expected Result</b></h3>

<p>The user should return to the same announcement position they were viewing before navigating to the feature.</p>

<h3><a name="ActualResult"></a><b>Actual Result</b></h3>

<p>The app resets to the first announcement instead of the previously viewed one.</p>

<h3><a name="Severity"></a><b>Severity</b></h3>

<p>Medium</p>
            <br/>
        </td>
